sql:
SELECT user_name 
FROM users 
WHERE user_id = (SELECT MAX(user_id) FROM users);

SELECT operator_name, operator_type
FROM operators
WHERE operator_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT o.operator_name
FROM operators o
JOIN performance_logs pl ON o.operator_id = pl.operator_id;

SELECT database_name 
FROM databases 
WHERE database_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
brief moment: execution time > 100 milliseconds; 
type of operation: DUPLICATE, NORMAL; 
status of the operation: KILLED, SUCCESSFUL; 
resources and performance metrics: JSON objects detailing CPU and memory usage, I/O operations, network latency.

sql:
SELECT dbms_name, version 
FROM dbms 
ORDER BY version DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "unique performers" refers to distinct operator names;
- "symphony of operations" is a metaphor for the operations being coordinated and logged in a systematic manner;
- "having contributed to at least one performance log" means the operators have entries in the 'performance_logs' table.

sql:
